Set on 1.25 acres with sweeping, unobstructed views of the Superstition Mountains, this home was designed for people who love being outdoors, entertaining friends, and soaking in every Arizona sunset. The sellers invested $150,000 into creating a backyard that truly has it all. At the center is a stunning 40x18 saltwater pool complete with a Baja shelf, sheer waterfall, bubblers, umbrella holders, and a sunken swim-up bar with a fridge and built-in BBQ. Whether you're hosting summer parties or enjoying quiet evenings under the open sky, this area feels like a getaway you never have to leave. Surrounding the pool is 2,600 sq. ft. of artificial lawn, beautiful custom Spanish tile, an in-ground trampoline, and a playhouse that makes the yard just as fun for kids as it is for adults. For those who love the idea of homestead living, you'll find raised garden beds, a large chicken coop, and a three-stall 10x10 mare motel equipped with a 1" water line and 20 AMP power ready for horses or future animals. And when the sun starts to set, the extended-length covered patio becomes the perfect place to unwind and take in those panoramic mountain views. Inside, the home is just as thoughtfully designed. The bright, open kitchen features extended-height cabinetry, an oversized island with built-in storage, matching stainless steel appliances, stylish pendant lights, a stainless vent hood, and a huge walk-in pantry. The wood-look tile, 10 ft ceilings, and abundance of natural light give the home a warm, modern feel. The primary suite is a peaceful retreat with a free-standing soaking tub, his-and-hers vanities, a glass-enclosed walk-in shower, and a huge walk-in closet. Bedrooms 2 and 3 are connected by a full Jack-and-Jill bathroom, offering privacy and convenience. A spacious laundry room with wall-to-wall cabinetry and an attached mudroom keeps everything organized. Additional upgrades round out the home, including a Kinetico water filtration system, energy-efficient dual-pane Low-E windows, 2x 50 amp EV charge outlets in the garage and a 9.2 kW solar system that produces roughly 16 megawatts annually helping keep utilities low. The 4-car garage, RV-friendly layout, and the freedom of no HOA give you space for toys, animals, and future ideas. The build was completed in 2020 and designed for both luxury and lifestyle, this home offers resort-style living, unforgettable mountain views, and the kind of indoor-outdoor experience people move to Arizona for.
